fields.value: Replication data for: An Introduction to the Augmented Inverse Propensity Weighted Estimator

publicationCitation.value: Adam N. Glynn and Kevin M. Quinn. 2010. "An Introduction to the Augmented Inverse Propensity Weighted Estimator." Political Analysis, 18: 36-56. article available here

files.description: This tarball should unpack into a directory called montecarlo that has four subdirectories: code, data, gendata, results.   montecarlo/gendata/gendata.R should be run first. This creates the Monte Carlo data and puts the Monte Carlo data in montecarlo/data/.   After the data has been created, the code in montecarlo/code/MatchingRun/ and montecarlo/code/notMatchingRun should be executed. Then montecarlo/code/plotdata2.R and montecarlo/code/summary.R should be run.   The R language for statistical computing is required to run this code.
